.TH "pack_sg_list" 9 "pack_sg_list" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pack_sg_list \- pack a scatter gather list from a linear buffer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pack_sg_list
.BI "(struct scatterlist *sg "  ","
.BI "int start "  ","
.BI "int limit "  ","
.BI "char *data "  ","
.BI "int count "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sg" 12
scatter/gather list to pack into
.IP "start" 12
which segment of the sg_list to start at
.IP "limit" 12
maximum segment to pack data to
.IP "data" 12
data to pack into scatter/gather list
.IP "count" 12
amount of data to pack into the scatter/gather list
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
sg_lists have multiple segments of various sizes.  This will pack
arbitrary data into an existing scatter gather list, segmenting the
data as necessary within constraints.
